#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:94
#: cf282c7efe6f45d8bf20d1b3098d1219
msgid "Can't use keyboard or mouse after creating sys-usb"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:97
#: dcb29975fd4f44ec84a22a5c522c6150
msgid ""
"You risk locking yourself out of your computer if you have a USB keyboard"
" and use full disk encryption alongside sys-usb. On boot, the keyboard "
"may be inactive, preventing you from entering your LUKS decryption "
"password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:99
#: 3e8542f4d17a4266b3e897f59c6230cd
msgid ""
"When you enable a USB qube, it hides all the USB controllers from dom0, "
"even before it gets started. So, if your only keyboard is on USB, you "
"should undo this hiding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:101
#: 9eda70ee805748eb9a3d858d8c1c6ab5
msgid ""
"To solve the problem, disable the USB qube by not having it autostart, or"
" unassigning your USB controller(s) from it. If you had created the USB "
"qube by checking the box in the installer, then your USB controller(s) "
"are probably hidden from dom0. To unhide them, reverse the procedure "
"described in :ref:`how to hide USB controllers from dom0 <user/advanced-"
"topics/usb-qubes:how to hide usb controllers from dom0>` (i.e., remove "
"``rd.qubes.hide_all_usb`` instead of adding it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:103
#: a03f54671141485bb197b3732d4a9fdc
msgid ""
"Note that this procedure will attach your USB controllers to dom0, so do "
"this only with USB devices you trust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:105
#: e2dbbfa0156a46b5a088cfae0749015a
msgid ""
"If your computer has a PS/2 port, you may instead use a PS/2 keyboard to "
"enter the LUKS password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:108
#: 7a49c331cdf048d18fc3a1fb8307f44b
msgid "\"qubes-usb-proxy not installed in the VM\" error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:111
#: e1206e08c3c44226994a35fdb75396b9
msgid ""
"When trying to :ref:`create and use a USB qube <user/how-to-guides/how-"
"to-use-usb-devices:creating and using a usb qube>` with the ``qubes-usb-"
"proxy`` package, you may receive this error: ``ERROR: qubes-usb-proxy not"
" installed in the VM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:113
#: 2344da93a57b470d85d192aef281d9a8
msgid ""
"If you encounter this error, you can install the ``qubes-usb-proxy`` with"
" the package manager in the VM you want to attach the USB device to. "
"Depending on your operating system, open a terminal in the template and "
"enter one of the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:115
#: b4a1f8a6624d4acf85fa3ac7f54f5c30
msgid "Fedora: ``sudo dnf install qubes-usb-proxy``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/usb-troubleshooting.rst:117
#: 7aec527fb71446a0a0024fb5c94dcabf
msgid "Debian/Ubuntu: ``sudo apt-get install qubes-usb-proxy``"
msgstr ""

